High profile radio personality, Robin Bailey has made her return to the airwaves, five weeks after husband Tony Smart took his own life, who was battling from depression.

The popular radio host, who works as a breakfast announcer for Brisbane based radio station 97.3 decided to return to work with her faithful team Terry and Bob saying she was so glad to be back.

With a box of tissues by her side, Bailey read out an emotional and teary prepared statement describing the tough last weeks since her husband's death, thanking all her family and friends, including her radio colleagues for their love during such a sad time.

